						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1332 (1410 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers the gift of <hi rend="bold">Kāṇiyāṭchi</hi> for sacred thread (<hi rend="italic">yajñōpavītam</hi>), a house, a share of offerings and two <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of tax-free land to Ellayar, son of Saṅgamadēvar of Kāśmīradēśa and belonging to Āśvalāyana-sūtra and Gautama-gōtra. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1332, Vikṛiti, Siṁha, ba. 3, Sunday, Uttiraṭṭādi</hi> regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1410, August 17, Sunday, ·87, ·28.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
